                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locusGrp>
                                        <locus from="Br" to="135v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="149r" to="328r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    </locusGrp>Gothic textualis.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="137r" to="148v" scheme="folios"/>Gothic textualis.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Ar" to="Ar" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page in black ink by an early modern hand: <quote>1566, 1424, 142, 566</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Cr" to="324v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Occasional marginal and interlinear additions in ink by several medieval hands. They consist of corrections, additions, glossing, and cross-references. Some leaves, e.g. <locus from="29r" to="51r" scheme="folios"/>, contain more extensive additions. On <locus from="308v" to="308v" scheme="folios"/> there is a longer addition.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Slip_collection_1r" to="Slip_collection_2v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>A large number of papers slips were originally placed between leaves as pagemarks. These slips contain text written by several contemporary hands. The text, ranging from 1-8 lines, seems to indicate passages on the leaves they were placed between. At some point the slips were removed and are now stored in two envelopes (<locus from="Envelope" to="Envelope" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="Note_1" to="Note_1" scheme="other"/>) attached to <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>. <locus from="Slip_identification_1" to="Slip_identification_3" scheme="other"/> indicate where the slips were previously placed. One slip stilll remains in its original place between <locus from="240" to="241" scheme="folios"/>. It reads:<quote> prosa de Sancta Affra Grates deo et honore</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in black ink, rubrics in red, capitals touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: opening decorated initial A over 7 lines in blue. The initial has reserved interior shapes and is surrounded by a complex flourishing and floral shapes in red. <locus from="274r" to="274r" scheme="folios"/>: plain chapter initial E over 6 lines in blue surrounded by a complex flourishing and floral shapes in red. <locus from="Br" to="Cv" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 2-3 lines in red. <locus from="1r" to="327r" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 1-5 lines in red, some with reserved interior shapes. Some initials, e.g. on <locus from="108r" to="108r" scheme="folios"/>, extend into the margin with a flourish. <locus from="47r" to="264r" scheme="folios"/>: penwork initials over 2 lines in black, touched in red or with red flourishing. Besides the main initial scheme consisting of different types of plain red initials and small penwork initials (most frequently on the top line), the manuscript
                                        also contains several sets of more idiosyncratic initals: <locus from="80r" to="80r" scheme="folios"/>: puzzle initial over 3 lines in red and black. <locus from="81r" to="81r" scheme="folios"/>: puzzle initial over 12 lines in red and black. The initial has reserved interior shapes and extends into the margin. <locus from="95r" to="95r" scheme="folios"/>: gold initial over 3 lines, placed on a green field. <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="99v" to="99v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="279v" to="279v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="321v" to="321v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="325v" to="325v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="327v" to="327v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        </locusGrp>: plain initials over 2 lines in black ink (perhaps a later addition?). <locus from="296v" to="296v" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 2 lines alternatig in blue, red, and green. <locus from="305v" to="305v" scheme="folios"/>: missing initial. <locus from="320r" to="321r" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 1 line in green. Ordo and canon missae: <locus from="137r" to="137r" scheme="folios"/>: decorated initial T over 6 lines. The letter body is made up of blue vegetative shapes that extend into a frame; the counterspace is filled in purple with diamonds and circles pattern in gold. From the initials three vines extend into the margins to form a frame. They are painted in purple, yellow and green. <locus from="137r" to="148r" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 1 line in blue or red.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="bookmarks">
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="137" to="137" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="139" to="139" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="141" to="141" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="143" to="143" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="145" to="145" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="147" to="147" scheme="folios"/>
                                        </locusGrp>: bookmarks/pagemarks in leather.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
                    </msPart>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
